# Nit Developer Tools for Eclipse

## Installing

For Eclipse Indigo

* In the main menu, go to "Help" then "Install New Software..."
* In the "Work with" fields, enter `http://nitlanguage.org/eclipse`
* Select the feature "Nit Developer Tools"

## Features

* Syntax highlighting on *.nit source files
* Background compiler to spot errors and warnings (require a working Nit environment)
* Nit perspective (FIXME: what does that bring)
* Nit project wizard

